    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.15.40"/>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">THOMAS L. MASSON
                        <lb/>
                    GLEN RIDGE, N.J.</hi>
                </fw>
                <opener>
                    <dateline>March 31- 1932</dateline>
                    <salute>My dear Mr Neihardt:</salute></opener> <p>I wish as many otherwise &#8212; let us hope &#8212; intelligent &#8212; people were far enough <add>along</add> to understand the reality of "Black Elk Speaks" as much as I have gotten it. I cannot but think that it is a permanent book &#8212; your poems are a source of joy to me. + this last book in particular gave me a real kick &#8212; the fact is that <unclear/> say the same thing &#8212; it just a difference in terms. Ever since I read your book I feel that I have been one with Black Elk.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours faithfully</salute>
                
                    <signed>Thomas L. Masson</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>Thank you so much
                    for your remembrance!</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
